         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">21 Novr 1881. ¶ R. Istituto di studi superiori in Firenze ¶ Museo Botanico ¶ My dear friend ¶  ¶ "Sir J. D. Hooker m'apprend la mort de Bentham. Voilà un grand travailleur de moins dans le champ de la...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.11.21</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Théodore Caruel</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller 1871-81, f. 338.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-style: italic; ">Annotated by M on the back of the folio</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">: Copy of Extract from a letter from Professor Caruel</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-style: italic; ">. (letter not found).</seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The copy is not in M’s hand. <seg style="color: #000000; ">It may have been included with</seg> M to J. Hooker, 31 December 1881 (in this edition as 81-12-31a).</p>
               </note>21 Novr 1881.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">R. Istituto di studi superiori in Firenze</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Museo Botanico</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear friend</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>"Sir J. D. Hooker m'apprend la mort de Bentham. Voilà un grand travailleur de moins dans le champ de la botanique systematique"<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>“Sir J. D. Hooker tells me of Bentham's death. That is one great worker fewer in the field of systematic </seg>botany”.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Such is textually the passage in a letter from Planchon of the 25th july, which led me to write to you, as I did.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Whence arose the mistake, I cannot say; as mistake it must be, since I have not seen the news anywhere. Let us therefore rejoice.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J. Hooker 19 September 1881 (in this edition as 81-09-19a), J. Hooker to M, 9 November 1881, and M to B. D. Jackson,<seg style="color: #0000ff; "> </seg>25 December 1881.<seg style="color: #000000; "> Bentham's wife, Sarah, died on 15 July 1881 (see B. Jackson (1906), p. 248); it seems likely that Hooker mentioned this in a letter to Planchon and that Planchon misunderstood what Hooker had told him. </seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
